<subSubSection id="49C942EEFFE3393BEBD2C1B0FE255C6E" pageId="77" pageNumber="78" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="016C1165FFE3393BEBD2C1B0FEAA5DAB" blockId="77.[227,341,1667,1693]" box="[227,341,1667,1693]" pageId="77" pageNumber="78">
<heading id="5A24A609FFE3393BEBD2C1B0FEAA5DAB" bold="true" box="[227,341,1667,1693]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="77" pageNumber="78" reason="3">
<emphasis id="33A7CD77FFE3393BEBD2C1B0FEAA5DAB" bold="true" box="[227,341,1667,1693]" pageId="77" pageNumber="78">Remarks</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="016C1165FFE3393BEBD2C181FE255C6E" blockId="77.[227,1437,1713,1880]" pageId="77" pageNumber="78">
<taxonomicName id="C6D36AE6FFE3393BEBD2C181FEAC5DFD" authorityName="Valenciennes" authorityYear="1833" box="[227,339,1714,1739]" class="Agaricomycetes" family="Russulaceae" genus="Lactarius" kingdom="Fungi" order="Russulales" pageId="77" pageNumber="78" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="33A7CD77FFE3393BEBD2C181FEAC5DFD" box="[227,339,1714,1739]" italics="true" pageId="77" pageNumber="78">Lactarius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was one of the most abundant otoliths in the collection. Two species were recognized, 
<taxonomicName id="C6D36AE6FFE3393BEEB4C181FEC75DD8" authorityName="Pomerol" authorityYear="1973" class="Agaricomycetes" family="Russulaceae" genus="Lactarius" kingdom="Fungi" order="Russulales" pageId="77" pageNumber="78" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="amplus">
<emphasis id="33A7CD77FFE3393BEEB4C181FA6A5DFD" box="[1413,1429,1714,1739]" italics="true" pageId="77" pageNumber="78">L</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="33A7CD77FFE3393BEBD2C1E7FEC75DD8" box="[227,312,1748,1774]" italics="true" pageId="77" pageNumber="78">amplus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="C6D36AE6FFE3393BEA48C1E6FE155DD8" baseAuthorityName="Dante &amp; Frizzell" baseAuthorityYear="1965" box="[377,490,1748,1774]" class="Agaricomycetes" family="Russulaceae" genus="Lactarius" kingdom="Fungi" order="Russulales" pageId="77" pageNumber="78" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="kokeni">
<emphasis id="33A7CD77FFE3393BEA48C1E6FE155DD8" box="[377,490,1748,1774]" italics="true" pageId="77" pageNumber="78">L. kokeni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(see below), the latter one being more abundant. Both species can be easily separated by the shape of their otoliths: 
<taxonomicName id="C6D36AE6FFE3393BE986C1CBFCD45C27" authorityName="Pomerol" authorityYear="1973" box="[695,811,1783,1810]" class="Agaricomycetes" family="Russulaceae" genus="Lactarius" kingdom="Fungi" order="Russulales" pageId="77" pageNumber="78" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="amplus">
<emphasis id="33A7CD77FFE3393BE986C1CBFD385C27" box="[695,711,1784,1809]" italics="true" pageId="77" pageNumber="78">L</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="33A7CD77FFE3393BE9E7C1C4FCD45C27" box="[726,811,1783,1809]" italics="true" pageId="77" pageNumber="78">amplus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has a horizontally more compressed outline (OL/OH = 1.15–1.33), whereas, in 
<taxonomicName id="C6D36AE6FFE3393BE928C028FD795C02" baseAuthorityName="Dante &amp; Frizzell" baseAuthorityYear="1965" box="[537,646,1818,1844]" class="Agaricomycetes" family="Russulaceae" genus="Lactarius" kingdom="Fungi" order="Russulales" pageId="77" pageNumber="78" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="kokeni">
<emphasis id="33A7CD77FFE3393BE928C028FD795C02" box="[537,646,1818,1844]" italics="true" pageId="77" pageNumber="78">L. kokeni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(OL/OH = 1.35–1.57), the posterior part of the otolith is markedly extended backwards.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="49C942EEFFE3393BEBD2C04CFC9F5338" pageId="77" pageNumber="78" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="016C1165FFE3393BEBD2C04CFD115CAF" blockId="77.[227,750,1919,1945]" box="[227,750,1919,1945]" pageId="77" pageNumber="78">
<heading id="5A24A609FFE3393BEBD2C04CFD115CAF" bold="true" box="[227,750,1919,1945]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="77" pageNumber="78" reason="3">
<emphasis id="33A7CD77FFE3393BEBD2C04CFD115CAF" bold="true" box="[227,750,1919,1945]" pageId="77" pageNumber="78">Stratigraphic and geographic distribution</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="016C1165FFE3393BEBD2C09DFC9F5338" blockId="77.[227,1436,1966,2062]" pageId="77" pageNumber="78">
Lutetian: Weches Formation and “Stone City beds”, 
<collectingRegion id="C317DF87FFE3393BE8B8C09DFC2E5CFE" box="[905,977,1966,1992]" country="United States of America" name="Texas" pageId="77" pageNumber="78">Texas</collectingRegion>
; Dobys Bluff Tongue of Kosciusko Formation, 
<collectingRegion id="C317DF87FFE3393BEA5DC0E2FE0A5CDD" box="[364,501,2001,2027]" country="United States of America" name="Mississippi" pageId="77" pageNumber="78">Mississippi</collectingRegion>
; Piney Point Formation, 
<collectingRegion id="C317DF87FFE3393BE82AC0E2FC815CDD" box="[795,894,2001,2027]" country="United States of America" name="Virginia" pageId="77" pageNumber="78">Virginia</collectingRegion>
. Bartonian: Cook Mountain Formation, 
<collectingRegion id="C317DF87FFE3393BEE69C0E2FA635CDD" box="[1368,1436,2001,2027]" country="United States of America" name="Texas" pageId="77" pageNumber="78">Texas</collectingRegion>
and 
<collectingRegion id="C317DF87FFE3393BEA24C0C7FE615338" box="[277,414,2036,2062]" country="United States of America" name="Mississippi" pageId="77" pageNumber="78">Mississippi</collectingRegion>
; “upper” Lisbon Formation, 
<collectingRegion id="C317DF87FFE3393BE9DFC0C7FCA35338" box="[750,860,2036,2062]" country="United States of America" name="Alabama" pageId="77" pageNumber="78">Alabama</collectingRegion>
.
</paragraph>
